@BenMcLean 
>  this is the **primary issue blocking**  Godot 4 from building programs for WebAssembly on .NET Core 5+.

Will [godot-dotnet](https://github.com/raulsntos/godot-dotnet) [helps ](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/70796#issuecomment-2121119041) to resolve this?

@GeorgeS2019 
> Will [godot-dotnet](https://github.com/raulsntos/godot-dotnet) [helps ](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/70796#issuecomment-2121119041) to resolve this?

No, It won't.

@lewing 
> The limitations of emscripten's dynamic linking have made it quite challenging for us to use in practice. Can you explain in more detail what problem you are attempting to solve? We use feedback to help prioritize work.

The Core issue for the Godot Game Engine is that we are embedding the dotnet into a C++ engine environment (either by hostfxr or loading NAOT pre-compiled library), which means there are bound to be two separate modules, the Godot Wasm and the dotnet Wasm+user assembly(s); and, as [the comment here](https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/70796#issuecomment-2524834258) explains, currently there is no way to dynamically link them (neither dotnet wasm as the main module nor dotnet wasm as the side module) like what we can do in every other platform.

The function common_call_trampoline() has below condition to set **_klass_** varibale in file **`mini-trampolines.c`**
		
```
if (m->is_inflated && (mono_method_get_context (m)->method_inst || mini_method_is_default_method (m))) {
	MonoMethodRuntimeGenericContext *mrgctx = (MonoMethodRuntimeGenericContext*)mono_arch_find_static_call_vtable (regs, code);

	klass = mrgctx->class_vtable->klass;
	method_inst = mrgctx->method_inst;
} else if ((m->flags & METHOD_ATTRIBUTE_STATIC) || m_class_is_valuetype (m->klass)) {
	MonoMethodRuntimeGenericContext *mrgctx = (MonoMethodRuntimeGenericContext*)mono_arch_find_static_call_vtable (regs, code);

	klass = mrgctx->class_vtable->klass;
	method_inst = mrgctx->method_inst;
	/*
	MonoVTable *vtable = mono_arch_find_static_call_vtable (regs, code);

	klass = vtable->klass;
	*/
} else {
	MonoObject *this_argument = (MonoObject *)mono_arch_get_this_arg_from_call (regs, code);

	actual_vt  = this_argument->vtable;
	vtable_slot = orig_vtable_slot;

	g_assert (m_class_is_inited (this_argument->vtable->klass));

	if (!vtable_slot) {
		mono_class_setup_supertypes (this_argument->vtable->klass);
		klass = m_class_get_supertypes (this_argument->vtable->klass) [m_class_get_idepth (m->klass) - 1];
	}
}
```
		
The failure case goes into the first if block and gets the currupted "**mrgctx**" from `mono_arch_find_static_call_vtable()` function which returns the value at **register r11**.

The first if block gets control because the value of "**_m->is_inflated_**" is true and "**_mono_method_get_context (m)->method_inst_**" gets some value.

We need to identify where and why the value for register r11 is getting updated.

CC: @uweigand @janani66

@uweigand  - moving your feedback here . The team will try to implement the OP_GENERIC_CLASS_INIT for ppc64le

(uweigand) "Maybe this is related to the fact that in the ppc backend there is no implementation of OP_GENERIC_CLASS_INIT, so it falls back to common code.  Now in principle this should also work, but no other platform uses the common code fallback any more, so maybe it doesn't always work correctly?

It probably cannot hurt to try providing an implementation of OP_GENERIC_CLASS_INIT and setting MONO_ARCH_HAVE_OP_GENERIC_CLASS_INIT to 1"

