### Description

I am porting a huge .NET application (a game written on a custom engine) to browser-wasm runtime. In release build we use AOT, and I noticed that in such configuration SBRK pointer slightly grows during app lifetime while managed heap size stays the same. Investigation with emscripten memory profiler helped me to find some problems, so listing them here. 

First is related to exceptions in AOT build. I tested also without AOT, and the problem is not reproduced in a simple release build. Also throwing exceptions from async tasks seems to leak more memory.

Repo with reproduction samples can be found [here](https://github.com/andrew-kulikov/dotnetwasm-bench?tab=readme-ov-file#running-sample). Samples are named "Exceptions" and "Async task exceptions". Sample code:
```cs
[JSExport]
public static async Task Exceptions(int count, bool doGc)
{
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
    {
        for (int j = 0; j < 100; j++)
        {
            try
            {
                throw new Exception($"Test exception {i * j}");
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {}
        }
        if (doGc)
        {
            DoGC();
        }
        PrintMemory($"#{i}");
        await Task.Delay(16);
    }
}

[JSExport]
public static async Task AsyncTaskExceptions(int count, bool doGc)
{
    for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
    {
        for (int j = 0; j < 10; j++)
        {
            await DoSomething().ContinueWith(t => t.Exception, TaskContinuationOptions.OnlyOnFaulted);
        }
        if (doGc)
        {
            DoGC();
        }
        PrintMemory($"#{i}");
        await Task.Delay(16);
    }

    async Task DoSomething()
